      "content": "Exactly. It feels like the whole idea of \"safety\" or \"moderation\" is just a code word for state-mandated censorship. If the internet is truly a spontaneous order, then any attempt to regulate it is essentially an attempt to kill the very thing that makes it valuable. Do you think most people realize how much of our freedom we're giving up when we accept these regulations?",
